<h2>What This Case Study Means for Your Program</h2>
<p>The 512-page programmatic SEO case study in this article is one data point. Your numbers will differ. Your timeline will differ. The patterns will not.</p>
<p>Indexing rates above 85% require phased launches and dense internal linking. Compounding curves bend at month 6 and steepen at month 9. The top 10% of pages will produce most of your revenue. The bottom 30% will produce almost none. Refresh sprints are not optional. Revenue tracks intent, not traffic volume.</p>
<p>You can build this system yourself, or you can have us build it for you. Either way, the numbers in this case study are reproducible if you respect the discipline.</p>
